{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the contract between manifest validation and execution gating: invalid manifest must prevent import/onLoad entirely. A pure Unit test of validator logic would miss regressions where loader still imports plugin code after validation failure. No real network/subprocess/OS primitive is required; a local temp plugin directory and real loader wiring is sufficient. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is only about validation + execution gate, not real subprocess/HTTP/AI output.","test_description":"Create a temp plugins directory with one plugin missing a required manifest field and an entry module with a visible side effect (e.g., writes marker file or increments shared counter). Run the real loader. Assert: loader reports manifest validation error; marker side effect never occurs; onLoad is never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's onLoad hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module ordering invariant between dependency resolver and lifecycle invoker. Unit-testing topological sort alone can miss wiring bugs where resolved order is not the invoked order. No real OS/network/subprocess dependency is required; local plugin fixtures and call-order capture are enough. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is only hook ordering across local plugins.","test_description":"Build two plugin fixtures in a temp directory: A depends on B. Each onLoad appends its name to a shared in-memory list or file. Run loader and assert call sequence is [\"B\",\"A\"].","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears at resolver->executor handoff: cycle detection must prevent any load attempts. Unit cycle-detection tests alone can miss executor still running despite detected cycle. No subprocess/network/AI dependency. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is graph-cycle reporting and local load suppression only.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies in manifest files. Run loader. Assert: cycle error is reported with A/B context; neither plugin entry module side effects run; neither onLoad is invoked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's onLoad hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Invariant spans module importer and lifecycle hook runner: import+module execution must complete before onLoad. Unit tests of hook runner or importer in isolation cannot catch sequencing bugs. Could require real Node import semantics, but still within in-process local modules/filesystem (not subprocess/real network), so Integration is minimum. Rejected System: behavior does not require subprocess/HTTP/external API; local Node runtime import is sufficient.","test_description":"Create a plugin entry module that sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` during module execution, and onLoad asserts that flag is already true (or records observed state). Run loader and assert onLoad sees initialized state; fail if onLoad runs before module execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its onLoad hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is orchestration across dependency graph + error isolation policy: one plugin failure should block only its dependents, not unrelated plugins. Unit tests of try/catch logic miss graph-aware continuation behavior. No real OS/network/subprocess or AI output involved. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is local initialization policy and dependency filtering.","test_description":"Create plugins: X (throws in onLoad), Y (depends on X), Z (independent). Run loader. Assert: X error is reported; Y is not initialized; Z onLoad is still invoked successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
